title: Norwalk Police seeking help identifying armed robbery suspects
title_page: Norwalk Police seeking help identifying armed robbery suspects
maintext:
NORWALK — Police are asking for the public’s help identifying two people connected to an armed robbery in Norwalk.
Two men committed the robbery near building 5 of Carlton Court, located at 133 Monterey Place, on June 13 at 7:36 p.m., police said in a statement. One of the men had a handgun, while the other had a taser.
The men stole cash and a cell phone before leaving the apartment complex in a black Toyota Camry with a New York license plate T610283C, police said. The car was driven by a third person.
Anyone with any information is asked to contact Det. Downer at 203-854-3182 or submit an anonymous tip at 203-854-311. Anonymous tips can also be left at www.norwalkpd.com or by texting “NPD” with the message to CRIMES (274637).
